search::addToSearchType()

Description
    public void search::addToSearchType(string $searchType, string $tableID)
    Checks whether or not $this->tablesUsed[$searchType] is set.  If not, creates the same as an array.  Checks array for the existence
    of $tableID.  If it doesn't, adds a table and, if necessary, linked tables.
Parameters
    searchType
	String variable specifying search type.

    tableID
	A string naming a table ID.

Examples
    <?php
	...
	$searchObj->addToSearchType("keyword",$tableID['instructors']);
	$searchObj->addToSearchType("class",$tableID['classes']);
	$searchObj->addToSearchType("instructor",$tableID['instructors']);
	...
    ?>
   
See Also
    search::addSearchType()
